# POLARIS — line-ending safety. Bash cannot execute CRLF scripts; Windows
# checkouts with core.autocrlf=true would otherwise rewrite them on clone.
#
# `polaris` and `VERSION` carry no extension, so they need path rules rather than a glob — and a
# pattern containing a slash is anchored to THIS file's directory, i.e. the repo root. That means
# each one needs naming TWICE: kit/ops/… is the product's source, and ops/… is the installation
# that runs this repo's own board. Both are real files; both are executed; both must stay LF.
* text=auto
kit/ops/polaris text eol=lf
kit/ops/VERSION text eol=lf
kit/ops/hooks/commit-msg text eol=lf
ops/polaris text eol=lf
ops/VERSION text eol=lf
ops/hooks/commit-msg text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
*.tsv text eol=lf
# Telemetry: append-only, union-merged, never eol-converted (init-board also arms this line).
ops/board/EVENTS.ndjson merge=union -text
